OL,6,FHowever, he said Methven could not
OL,7,Fexplain why it happened, and added:
OL,8,F"He has flashbacks but no real memory
OL,9,Fas to how things progressed to this
OL,10,Fdestruction of human life."
OL,12,FImposing a life sentence, Judge Lord
OL,13,FMatthews said Methven had admitted a
OL,14,F"truly dreadful crime".
OL,16,FLord Matthews said: "At 21 years old,
OL,17,Fshe was standing at the threshold of
OL,18,Fwhat should have been a long and
OL,19,Ffulfilling life. You were a trusted
OL,20,Fmember of her family but betrayed that
OL,21,Ftrust.
